Ñ Ð Ð¾ÐÐ Astra B  The Films and Programs Resonating with Fans at Comic Con Ð Ñ Ð¾Ð Ñ Ð Ð Ð Ñ Ñ Ñ ÐºÑ Ñ Ñ Ñ       Another summer another San Diego Comic Con come and gone We used our syndicated metrics such as the ListenFirst Interest Score and Social Engagement to analyze consumer interest and interactions on social and digital channels during Comic Con  What series and films sparked the the most conversation among fans It turns out Interest for films were stronger than for TV programs this year with the Top  by Interest Score dominated by films Superhero film Aquaman made waves at Comic Con with an unbeatable streak driving the most search social conversation and YouTube video views In fact Warner Bros released the most digital and social assets online after their panel with trailers for Aquaman Shazam Fantastic Beasts The Crimes of Grindelwald and Godzilla King of the Monsters available for viewing immediately after the panel which generated significant ongoing interest and drove these films into the Top  Overall for Interest Score As always across film and TV superheroes and sci fi dominated the excitement at Comic Con and a strong digital social strategy like WB was critical for carrying the momentum post show As for TV interest for AMC s The Walking Dead was mostly related to announcements made about key characters leaving the show this season The series also scored the highest volume of cross channel responses coming off the release of their latest trailer for Season  Doctor Who also came in strong with conversation centering around the announcement of Jodie Whittaker as the first female Doctor in the series history And for American Horror Story FX released a unique AR experience that drove the program into the  spot Overall Aquaman saw the highest YouTube video views for its trailer following the Comic Con panel with  M views followed by Glass which saw  M trailer views on YouTube over the weekend While film took top ranks on Interest TV dominated Social Engagement Scores with super fandoms like those of The Walking Dead and Riverdale swarming to newly published content for a glimpse at new trailers and cast interviews The CW swept the competition  programs making the Top  ranker while Warner Bros is the only film studio to break the Top  with Fantastic Beasts The Crimes of Grindelwald and Aquaman at  and  respectively Fantastic Beasts The Crimes of Grindelwald was the most engaging film of Comic Con based on responses across Facebook Twitter and Instagram alone with fans racing to watch and discuss the newly released trailer AMC s The Walking Dead saw the highest cross channel social engagement of all TV and Films driven by high volume of responses on Instagram with the channel contributing  of total engagement Posts focusing on cast relationships and character development for the upcoming season garnered the greatest response from fans Following The Walking Dead is Riverdale with the show primarily generating engagement through Instagram as well accounting for  of Riverdale s total social engagement during Comic Con Reposts of cast content like from actress Mädchen Amick surfaced as are most popular with Amick s posts coming in as the top two most engaging from Riverdale s SDCC content Sourcing The data presented here represents the rankings as of July   to  pm PT on July   ListenFirst Interest Score is the sum of search and conversation Wikipedia page views and hashtag handle mentions Social Engagement Score measures all public engagement across all Social Data Channels for the following types of activity Fan Growth Content Responses and Conversation Volume Ð ÐµÑ ÐµÐÑ Ð Ðº Ð½Ð¾ÐÐ¾Ñ Ñ Ð Ð Ð Ñ Ñ ÐµÐÑ Ðµ Ñ Ð Ð¾ÐÐ China Academy of Space Technology   New Shows to Watch This Summer Ð Ñ Ð¾Ð Ñ Ð Ð Ð Ñ Ñ Ñ ÐºÑ Ñ Ñ Ñ       It s typical at this point for each new season of television to feature a slate of movie stars making the transition onto the small screen and this summer is no exception serving up Kevin Costner Hugh Grant Amy Adams Guy Pearce and John Krasinski among others What does feel noteworthy is the glaring lack of diversity on multiple fronts among the freshmen series debuting over the next few months With the exceptions of Ryan Murphy s Pose and Marti Noxon s Dietland TV s new summer offerings are defined by dynastic family feuds spy thrillers well bred detectives and dysfunctional superpowered teens In other words The same stories that always get told only this time with A list names attached Standing in contrast are the shows returning with new episodes most of which found success not by sticking to the script but imagining a new one New shows reboots and revivals Cinemax C B Strike Cinemax June  Cinemax gets the BBC adaptation of the Cormoran Strike detective novels published by the somewhat famous author J K Rowling under the less famous pseudonym Robert Galbraith The seven episodes follow Strike Tom Burke a British private investigator and military veteran as he tackles three confounding mysteries FX Pose FX June  The insanely prolific Ryan Murphy s newest drama is set amid s New York s vogue ball scene and co produced with the writer and activist Janet Mock Pose tells the stories of the LGBT performers and outcasts who find a thriving artistic community and makeshift family on the dancefloor HBO Succession HBO June  Is Jesse Armstrong s In the Loop The Thick of It new HBO series about the children vying for a piece of their media mogul father s empire based on the Murdochs The Redstones The Trumps Either way Brian Cox
